Creating Datasets and Trending Dashboards from Salesforce Reports

By creating trending CRM Analytics dashboards that track key metrics over time, you make sense of growing, ever-changing datasets. Trending data in CRM Analytics helps discover hidden insights and share them with colleagues.

When creating a trending dashboard based on a Salesforce report, CRM Analytics generates a dataset and a dashboard based on the underlying Salesforce data.

Trending refers to data displayed over a timeline, allowing trends and patterns to emerge. Any regularly updated dataset with dates associated with it (a date or timestamp attribute for each row) can be trended.

Start Trending Salesforce Reports
Review our guidelines when trending Salesforce Reports.
Stop Trending Salesforce Reports to remain under the limit.
Share Trending Dashboards just like any CRM Analytics dashboard.
Limits and Limitations for Trending Data in Analytics are in place to prevent performance degradation.
